node.text: Meet my WORLD FAMOUS SCIENTISTS 👩🏿‍🔬👩🏻‍🔬👩🏼‍🔬🧑🏾‍🔬🧑🏻‍🔬👨🏼‍🔬This is one of my absolute favorite lessons I do all year & I love to start with it right at the beginning of the year to make a big impact on my students!! Most times when they come to me in 6th grade they have hardly had any science before. Being in my science lab is the first time they are exposed to all things science✨This means they come to me with lots of stereotypes of what science is, who can do science, & what a scientist looks likes. Through this lesson they discover that THEY will be the scientists in our classroom this year & anybody can be a scientist no matter what they look like👏🏼👏🏾👏🏿😍 I will say that I had the most diverse drawings of scientists this year than I ever have before!!! (& by most I mean 23/135 students drew females🙃😅)

node.text: What they think a scientist looks like vs what a scientist actually looks like😉👩🏻‍🔬🧑🏾‍🔬👨🏼‍🔬👩🏿‍🔬We did 1/2 of my “WHAT IS A SCIENTIST” lesson today & it made my heart so full💛 The students wrote character traits, what scientists wear, examples of scientists, & described what they looked like on notecards. Then they combined notecards with their table & had 5 minutes to build the tallest tower. The winning group with the tallest free standing tower after 5 minutes wins!! We will complete the 2nd half of this lesson on Monday. This 2 day lesson is in my TpT store & includes scientists, historians, mathematicians, artists, writers, & musicians!

node.text:
📓NOTEBOOK SETUP DAY📓 Yesterday we set up our science interactive notebooks! I am a die hard interactive notebook fan. I’ve been using them for 6 years & have never looked back! I don’t do the crazy cutting & folding. I tell my students that their notebooks act like their homemade textbooks they create throughout the entire year! By the end of the year they have a “textbook” of everything they’ve learned that year!! Over the years I’ve learned a few things so here are my tips:

📓Make dividers with tabs for each unit. Every time you start a new unit, the students add in a new divider!
📓Notebooks stay in the classroom. Their lockers are a disaster & I found that the notebooks didn’t last all year when they kept them in their locker! (They can take them home to study for quizzes/tests)
📓Each class has their own color. I put a piece of duct tape that color on the spine as they are decorating their cover. If a notebook is on the floor I immediately know what class it belongs to!
📓First student in the class dumps the notebooks on the counter & spreads them out. This reduces congestion at the notebook bins. 
📓Have a “tidy tub” to put scraps in at their table. This reduces scraps on the floor!

I have an entire blog post on interactive notebooks with more information as well! You can get these science covers & dividers in my TPT store! Let me know if you have any other questions!!

🌟Bonding with Bensko🌟 This is a lesson that incorporates science skills while they are still getting to know ME! There were 10 brown bags around the room. The students had to make 2 observations on every object inside the bag. Then they would make 1 inference on how the object related to me! It’s so funny to hear what they come up with!!🤣 I like putting in a few difficult items to confuse them & not make it easy! This is a great get to know the teacher lesson that also incorporates a little bit of science. I also have a digital version of this called Examine the Teacher on TpT! Here’s what I put in the bags:

✨Starbucks apron: I love Starbucks/coffee (they think it means I worked at Starbucks🤣)
✨ A quarter & 3 pennies: add it up & that’s my age
✨American flag: my birthday is the 4th of July
✨Mini hot sauce: I love spicy food🌶
✨Picture of little girls: my nieces (this one always confuses them & I love hearing them argue about if I have kids or not🤣
✨Toy airplane: I like to travel
✨GYTO patch: some students saw my GYTO sticker on my laptop & got it👏🏼
✨Cubs lanyard: Go Cubs
✨Sour gummy worms: fav candy
✨Whisk: I like to cook

node.text:
Decided to add a little bit of ✨spice✨ to my classroom management system!! I’ve been using the Jolly Rancher Wars for the last 3 years in my middle school classroom & it works like a charm!! I’m honestly shocked at what a student will do for one Jolly Rancher🤣 

Jolly Rancher Wars is a weekly challenge where my 5 science classes compete against each other.! They have opportunities to earn points throughout the class for positive behaviors. They can also lose points as a class for being too loud or off task. At the end of the week, whatever class has the most points wins!! Then the following Monday every student in the winning class gets a Jolly Rancher. Yup, that’s literally it! 

For the last few years I hand wrote it on my white board in the front of my classroom. (Swipe to see what I used to do) I decided to spice✨ it up a little bit! You can get these fully editable labels in my TpT store. I also just wrote a blog post on all the details of this classroom management system! Head to maniacsinthemiddle.com to check it out!

node.text: It’s almost time to GET MY ACTUAL TEACH ON🥳 One week from today I will have a classroom full of students for the first time since March of 2020. No students will be online (no simultaneous teaching😭🙌🏼) & everyone will be masked. Is it back to normal? Absolutely not. But it is the closest thing to normal teaching I’ve had in a long time. I cannot wait to do hands on science lessons with a classroom full of students again😭💕 Hoping this year will fill up my teacher cup a little since last year definitely emptied it. When is your first day with students & what are you looking forward to the most this school year?! Let me know!!
